<head>SHORT</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>BREVITAS</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">短</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">短</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SMALL in THE MOST LONG HORIZONTAL DIMENSION.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general term for shortness is duǎn 短 (ant. cháng 長 "long").</p>
<p>2. Jìng 徑 refers specifically to the shortness of a walking distance or a travelling distance.</p>
<p>NB: Cuó 矬 and ǎi 矮 "of short stature" are apparently post-Han (NANBEICHAO/SONG).</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>短</p>
<p>短小</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
